description:
Yariv reagent is a set of organic compounds that bind arabinogalactan proteins via &szlig;-D-(1-&gt;3)-galactan structures. Structural basis of these complexes is poorly understood. Here we provide the results of a series of molecular dynamics simulations of systems containing &szlig;-D-Gal-Yariv reagent molecules and/or &szlig;-D-(1-&gt;3)-linked 
tri- or hexasaccharide of galactose. Our motivation was to elucidate structure of Yariv-arabinogalactan assemblies. 

 &nbsp;

